  "code": "timeline\n        title England's History Timeline\n        section Stone Age\n          7600 BC : Britain's oldest known house was built in Orkney, Scotland\n          6000 BC : Sea levels rise and Britain becomes an island.<br> The people who live here are hunter-gatherers.\n        section Bronze Age\n          2300 BC : People arrive from Europe and settle in Britain. <br>They bring farming and metalworking.\n                  : New styles of pottery and ways of burying the dead appear.\n          2200 BC : The last major building works are completed at Stonehenge.<br> People now bury their dead in stone circles.\n                  : The first metal objects are made in Britain.Some other nice things happen. it is a good time to be alive.\n",
  "diagram_type": "timeline size:600..900",
  "collected_at": "2026-02-27T04:01:32.616209",
  "cscw_dialogue": [
    {
      "turn_id": 1,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "propose",
      "utterance": "我们来做一个英格兰历史的时间轴吧，从石器时代开始。最早的事件我想放7600 BC，奥克尼群岛那边发现了英国已知最古老的房子。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Stone Age section",
        "7600 BC",
        "Orkney, Scotland",
        "Britain's oldest known house"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 2,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "clarify",
      "utterance": "奥克尼是在苏格兰，不是英格兰本土，这个地理关系需要特别说明吗？还有下一个节点我想到6000 BC海平面上升、英国成为岛屿这件事，可以和狩猎采集者的生活方式放在一起。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "6000 BC",
        "Sea levels rise",
        "Britain becomes an island",
        "hunter-gatherers"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 3,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "对，奥克尼虽然地理上偏，但确实是英国历史的一部分。6000 BC那个节点可以写两行：海平面上升成为岛屿，以及当时人们还是狩猎采集者。接下来进入青铜时代吧，2300 BC是个关键转折点。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Bronze Age section",
        "2300 BC"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 4,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "execute",
      "utterance": "好，2300 BC我记录了：人们从欧洲来到英国定居，带来了农耕和金属冶炼技术。另外同一时期还有新的陶器风格和丧葬方式出现，这个放在同一节点的第二行可以吗？",
      "elements_involved": [
        "2300 BC",
        "People arrive from Europe",
        "farming and metalworking",
        "pottery",
        "burying the dead"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 5,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "propose",
      "utterance": "可以。然后2200 BC是巨石阵最后的大型建造工程完工，同时人们开始在石圈中埋葬死者。这个节点也有两个层面的信息。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "2200 BC",
        "Stonehenge",
        "building works completed",
        "stone circles",
        "bury their dead"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 6,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "clarify",
      "utterance": "2200 BC这个节点如果拆成两行，第一行放巨石阵和丧葬习俗，第二行我想补充金属制品首次在英国制造的信息。不过后面还有一句\"Some other nice things happen\"，这个表述是不是太口语化了？",
      "elements_involved": [
        "2200 BC",
        "first metal objects",
        "Some other nice things happen"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 7,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "repair",
      "utterance": "确实，那句太随意了。但保留一点轻松的语气也可以，改成\"Some other nice things happen. It is a good time to be alive.\"吧，既点明了这是繁荣时期，又不至于太学术。金属制品那句放在第二行开头。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "2200 BC",
        "first metal objects are made in Britain",
        "Some other nice things happen",
        "it is a good time to be alive"
      ],
      "is_repair": true
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 8,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "明白了，2200 BC节点最终是：第一行巨石阵完工和石圈丧葬，第二行首批金属制品制造，加上那句对时代氛围的描述。整个时间轴从石器时代到青铜时代，涵盖了建筑、技术和社会变迁，结构清晰。",
      "elements_involved": [
